ing the scenarios when `/api/v1/auth/me` fails by clearing invalid tokens and checking for a valid preview session from Phase 4, keeping it only as a fallback. I'm focusing on cleaning the session if no token is present.\n\n\n**Defining Access Boundaries**\n\nI'm now carefully defining role-based route access, prioritizing the core rules. I've confirmed that client roles are restricted from `/admin` and will get the \"Access Restricted\" page. I'm focusing on ensuring admin roles don't inadvertently access `/portal` routes, keeping hydration safety in mind. I'm clarifying what happens if a GFF Admin tries to access the portal. Also, if there's no session, I'll clear it and set loading to false.\n\n\n**Evaluating Access Permissions**\n\nI'm now investigating potential access restrictions for GFF admins and staff to `/portal` routes, particularly considering the implications of `canAccessPortalSection`. My goal is to ensure that GFF admins can still access the client portal section, even with the new access rules. I'm focusing on clarifying whether they should be redirected or blocked from `/portal` routes.\n\n\n**Confirming Route Accessibility**\n\nI'm now confirming the rules. I've reconfirmed that clients cannot access `/admin`, and admins cannot inadvertently access `/portal`. I'm verifying the GFF Admin access to `/portal` as a simulation, aiming to maintain the Phase 4 premium feature.\n\n\n"}}
