{"ts":"2026-06-27T14:20:39.860Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Evaluating Access Control**\n\nI'm currently focused on integrating the new strict RBAC rules into the `handleBypass` function. Specifically, I'm working to ensure that when `type` is \"portal,\" access control adheres to the defined client roles (`client_admin`, `client_member`) or the `gff_admin` role. The goal is to enforce the right level of access, particularly for portals.\n\n\n**Refining Role Definitions**\n\nI'm now revising the logic for determining authorized roles. I'm focusing on the `getAuthorizedRoles` function and updating its filters. For portal access, I'm ensuring roles are either client-based or `gff_admin`. For admin sections, I'm restricting access to admin roles like those starting with `gff_`, or the specialized roles such as `finance_admin`, `support_agent`, and `viewer`. The goal is to enforce these access rules precisely.\n\n\n**Validating Security Boundaries**\n\nI've just validated a key security boundary. Client roles are correctly restricted from admin routes; they can't bypass into client roles from an admin section. This ensures only GFF admin and operator roles can bypass within admin routes, creating high security.\n\n\n**Confirming Logging Consistency**\n\nI'm verifying the synchronization of console log warnings with session checks in `PreviewRouteGuard.tsx`, focusing on lines 135-165. The `useEffect` hook dynamically logs based on the `session` and `hasAccess` variables. It appears the logging is already consistently tied to the real-time access control status. No changes seem needed.\n\n\n**Implementing Session Verification**\n\nI'm now implementing the edited code for `PreviewRouteGuard.tsx` to handle session verification. I am replacing lines 118-132, and this change enables asynchronous API calls for authentication. This ensures that the system accurately reflects the current API state and correctly blocks unauthorized access.\n\n\n**Refactoring `useEffect` Hooks**\n\nI'm now refactoring the `useEffect` hooks in `PreviewRouteGuard.tsx` to handle `handleBypass` and `getAuthorizedRoles` more efficiently. I'm focusing on lines 208-236, as well as considering combining with a prior change or maintaining as separate edits, I will look at the best way to modify lines 133 to 207 to ensure the new logic integrates cleanly and reliably. The goal is to optimize both for future scalability, and reliability, with only minimal impact to the original code.\n\n\n**Optimizing Concurrency & Verification**\n\nI'm now focusing on optimizing concurrency and validating code regions. I'm verifying the exact text within the regions I intend to edit, to prevent any conflicts during the refactor. I'm especially focused on the `useEffect` block, ensuring that session and access rules are consistently synchronized. I've confirmed that separate editor calls are appropriate.\n\n\n**Integrating Session Updates**\n\nI'm now integrating the session update logic. I'm adding `useEffect` with an asynchronous `verify` function to check `/api/v1/auth/me`. This updates the session and access on `gff_preview_session_changed` event. I'm also ensuring the correct token and content type are sent in the headers.\n\n```\n\n**Implementing Session Refresh**\n\nI'm now integrating the session refresh logic within the `PreviewRouteGuard`. I'm focusing on the `useEffect` block to handle session updates. I've added a try-catch block to verify the token with the `/api/v1/auth/me` endpoint. If successful, I'm updating the session in local storage. I'm also ensuring to clear the tokens if authentication fails. The goal is to accurately maintain the local session based on API verification. I also have added logic to fall back to the cached session if the backend authentication fails.\n\n\n**Updating Session Access Logic**\n\nI'm now incorporating logic to enhance session management within `PreviewRouteGuard`. I've added a section that prioritizes a valid cached session if mock mode is active, or if a token is present. I'm also refining session-based access determination, and evaluating role-specific access, for both \"portal\" and \"admin\" types. The checks for access are now being done more efficiently.\n\n\n**Refining Bypass Handling**\n\nI'm now revising the bypass logic to prioritize direct routing if the role is authorized. I am examining and testing the `handleBypass` function in `PreviewRouteGuard.tsx` to handle the new session updates and the verification for authorization more effectively. This ensures that the user remains on the exact page they requested, or is cleanly re-routed to a dashboard.\n\n\n**Refining Bypass Functionality**\n\nI'm now revising the `handleBypass` function in `PreviewRouteGuard.tsx` to handle more dynamic routing. I'm focusing on ensuring users can stay on their exact path after bypass if authorized. I've integrated checks for client roles versus admin roles. I'm allowing for a direct route if the new role is authorized, with the goal of more seamless and intelligent handling.\n\n\n**Enhancing Role-Based Routing**\n\nI'm now refining the logic in `handleBypass`. I'm focusing on clean routing based on authorization: if a role is permitted, I'm routing directly to the requested path. Otherwise, I'm defaulting to the appropriate dashboard (\"portal\" or \"admin\"). This includes considering client versus admin roles, and more efficient navigation.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T14:20:39.864Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"k7ottefn","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/components/private-app/PreviewRouteGuard.tsx","old_text":"  // Sync session and access rules\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!mounted) return;\n    const verify = () => {\n      const s = getPreviewSession();\n      setSession(s);\n      const sec = pathname.split(\"/\")[2] || \"dashboard\";\n      setActiveSec(sec);\n      setHasAccess(type === \"portal\" ? canAccessPortalSection(s?.role || \"viewer\", sec) : canAccessAdminSection(s?.role || \"viewer\", sec));\n      setLoading(false);\n    };\n    verify();\n    window.addEventListener(\"gff_preview_session_changed\", verify);\n    return () => window.removeEventListener(\"gff_preview_session_changed\", verify);\n  }, [pathname, type, mounted]);","new_text":"  // Sync session and access rules using backend auth /api/v1/auth/me and stored MVP token\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!mounted) return;\n\n    let isSubscribed = true;\n\n    const verify = async () => {\n      const token = localStorage.getItem(\"gff_ai_access_token\");\n      const sec = pathname.split(\"/\")[2] || \"dashboard\";\n      if (isSubscribed) {\n        setActiveSec(sec);\n      }\n\n      let currentSession: PreviewSession | null = null;\n\n      if (token) {\n        try {\n          const res = await fetch(\"/api/v1/auth/me\", {\n            headers: {\n              \"Authorization\": `Bearer ${token}`,\n              \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"\n            }\n          });\n\n          if (res.ok) {\n            const data = await res.json();\n            if (data.success && data.user) {\n              const u = data.user;\n              currentSession = {\n                name: u.name,\n                email: u.email,\n                role: u.role as PreviewRole,\n                clearance: u.clearance || \"CLEARANCE LEVEL III (SANDBOX OPERATOR)\",\n                isMock: false,\n                label: `REST-API AUTH: ${u.clientAssociation || \"Core\"}`\n              };\n              localStorage.setItem(\"gff_ai_preview_session_v1\", JSON.stringify(currentSession));\n            }\n          } else {\n            // Token is invalid or expired\n            localStorage.removeItem(\"gff_ai_access_token\");\n            localStorage.removeItem(\"gff_api_token\");\n          }\n        } catch (err) {\n          console.error(\"Failed to verify token with /api/v1/auth/me, trying cached session\", err);\n        }\n      }\n\n      // Fall back to local preview session if backend auth didn't produce one\n      if (!currentSession) {\n        const cached = getPreviewSession();\n        // Keep Phase 4 preview mode only as fallback if explicitly needed\n        if (cached && (cached.isMock || token)) {\n          currentSession = cached;\n        }\n      }\n\n      if (isSubscribed) {\n        setSession(currentSession);\n\n        if (currentSession) {\n          const role = currentSession.role;\n          const isClient = role === \"client_admin\" || role === \"client_member\";\n          const isAdmin = [\"gff_admin\", \"gff_operator\", \"finance_admin\", \"support_agent\", \"viewer\"].includes(role);\n\n          let allowed = false;\n          if (type === \"portal\") {\n            // Client roles can access portal, and gff_admin can access for simulation override\n            if (isClient || role === \"gff_admin\") {\n              allowed = canAccessPortalSection(role, sec);\n            }\n          } else if (type === \"admin\") {\n            // Admin roles can access admin\n            if (isAdmin) {\n              allowed = canAccessAdminSection(role, sec);\n            }\n          }\n          setHasAccess(allowed);\n        } else {\n          setHasAccess(false);\n        }\n\n        setLoading(false);\n      }\n    };\n\n    verify();\n\n    const handleSessionChanged = () => {\n      verify();\n    };\n\n    window.addEventListener(\"gff_preview_session_changed\", handleSessionChanged);\n    return () => {\n      isSubscribed = false;\n      window.removeEventListener(\"gff_preview_session_changed\", handleSessionChanged);\n    };\n  }, [pathname, type, mounted]);"}}}
