{"ts":"2026-06-27T14:22:13.528Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Verifying Code Cleanliness**\n\nI'm incredibly pleased to report that `npm run lint` completed flawlessly! The codebase seems exceptionally clean, and our changes adhere completely to established linting and compiler standards. Now, my focus shifts to exploring potential backend-specific tasks or overlooked files to ensure comprehensive coverage.\n\n\n**Implementing Auth Guards**\n\nI've successfully updated the private route guards to leverage the backend authentication state, as well as the cached MVP token from `/auth/me`. I'm pleased to confirm the `gff_ai_access_token` check and secure asynchronous verification request are now implemented, with local state and preview session updates based on backend API responses. I've also verified that the landing page and GFF AI tool sections have been left untouched.\n\n\n**Refining Route Access Controls**\n\nI've finalized the access controls for both `/portal/*` and `/admin/*` routes. I can confirm the logic enforces role-based access; clients can only access `/portal`, and admins can access `/admin`. Unauthorized users are now gracefully redirected to either `/portal/login` or `/admin/login`, and an informative \"Access Restricted\" page is displayed for forbidden access attempts. I'm pleased with the robustness of this implementation.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T14:22:13.531Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"u18o49qr","input":{"summary":"1. **Page/Section Narrative**: Enhanced the private route guards (`components/private-app/PreviewRouteGuard.tsx`) to connect with the backend authentication system by verifying stored MVP tokens with the `/api/v1/auth/me` endpoint.\n2. **Strict RBAC Constraints**:\n   - Enforced client-specific routes (`/portal/*`) such that only users with Client roles (`client_admin`, `client_member`) or GFF Admin role (`gff_admin` for simulation) can gain access.\n   - Enforced admin-specific routes (`/admin/*`) such that only GFF internal/admin roles (`gff_admin`, `gff_operator`, `finance_admin`, `support_agent`, `viewer`) can gain access.\n   - Forbidden role combinations automatically display a premium, red-accented 'Clearance Insufficient' restricted segment page.\n3. **Graceful Fallbacks & Redirects**:\n   - Unauthorized users are shown a polished 'Clearance Required' Decoupled state with a 5-second auto-redirect countdown to `/portal/login` or `/admin/login`.\n   - Maintained Phase 4 local preview session as an explicit fallback when backend tokens are absent or invalid.\n4. **Hydration & Safety**:\n   - Enforced strict hydration checks via `mounted` state guards.\n   - Implemented async token verifications inside `useEffect` with standard cleanup handlers to ensure fast UX and prevent infinite redirect loops.\n5. **Quality Checks**:\n   - Clean compilation verified via `npx tsc --noEmit`.\n   - Clean code format verified via ESLint (`npm run lint`), passing with zero warnings or errors.\n   - Verified that landing page files and GFF AI tools were untouched.","verified":true}}}
